<br>
I take offense at the comment &quot;UBER soandso's cause ...&quot; That is one of those wonderful blanket statement slams that gets fed into the mainstream mentality. I am not 60 yet, I don't have my epic, most of the guild members I raid with are above me in gear and levels - and at 54, I am a youngster within these ranks, so not UBER. Yet, travelling to and fro, at 54, I am an UBER compared to the majority of the server .. and I deal with people, no matter level, with the same respect and consideration for their time and concerns as I did when I started at level 1. It is called common courtesy. It is called being polite. It is maintaining my character - in Norrath - in a manner that I would like to think is how a 'fantasy realm' should be ... just a tad better than RL.<br>
<br>
Then again, that is my choice, and for those who choose to travel the dark side, that is their choice. I am not going to climb on a moralistic pedastal and proclaim who is the better for it - nor should anyone else. If it has gotten to the point of degrading your game play because of what others are doing, you are taking this way to serious. Leaving the game is a good idea - take a break and get some perspective.<br>
<br>
For example - if you are doing your best to set the positive image in game doesn't it actually help to have someone's alter ego floating around doing just the opposite? To those who share your image of game play they have a mentor, or example to strive to become. And vice versa. End result is those of similar habits, conduct and outlook towards the game gravitate towards each other and as a result find their cliques and enjoy the game in their own way. This is good - regardless of your personal conflict with their style not being yours.<br>
<br>
Not to slam LoS - but using them as the example all others like to use - the reaction to their 'actions' by the rest of the server is commendable. Commendable in the sense that not one of the other UBER guilds has stepped across the line with the point of view that if LoS is going to do this, then so are we. In fact, guilds have become more aware of their need to build solid reputations, conduct themselves with integrity and step outside of themselves to ensure that rotations, the calendar and general agreements between each other are kept sacred. If anything - regardless of the validity of the claims against LoS, but because the perception of these claims - this has brought to light what the deterioration of communication and fairplay would do to the server and we should thank them.<br>
<br>
And we should also get off the high horse regarding LoS. Obviously they (generically the guild) are a strong band of folks who get along - what they are doing is working for them. A lot of guilds, no matter the size, cannot honestly say they are as emotionally strong and solid internally as LoS.<br>
<br>
While the argument sounds nice when placed in the 'treaties' and 'sanctions' terminology of political jargon ... in another context, using words such as 'ignore' and 'blackball,' paints this same argument as both short sighted and childish in its effort to coordinate a server wide ban against LoS. Ironically ... well, not really ironic, but more so pathetically, from a historical perspective the Nazis utilized the same argument in developing a national hatred of Jews based completely on the mass propoganda of them as a 'group' (race) who controlled the money behind the scenes. They made them dangerous to the masses - much of what is being done to LoS here ... except to eventually toss Chakin into one of the Norrathian ovens prolly would get a 'this combination does not combine' message.<br>
<br>
Bottom line: get a grip. When LoS actions hit the RL 6 o'clock new we can be concerned.<br>
